review_blob:
Pours a deep golden orange. Grapefruit and orange dominate the aroma, with hints of sweet malt. Drinks crisp and smooth. Bitter orange zest on the aftertaste. Not what I was expecting for an extra pale but enjoyable. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Been wanting to try for a while, finally found some cans at BevMo. Pours pitch black into a tulip. Nice aroma of chocolate, coffee and booze. So yummy!  Sweet toffee and mocha with nice bitter after taste. Really smooth feel and fills your mouth with flavor. Very nice, but there are comparable choices for a lot less $.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle to tulip. Pitch black, small head. Great aroma of chocolate, toffee, coffee and booze. Tastes all balanced nicely with a smooth feel and slightly bitter and warming aftertaste. Great flavor, great balance. Great beer. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

6th anniversary edition. 22 oz bottle into a pint glass. Thick and black with small brown head. Not much lacing. Smells great - very different with the expected toffee and bitter chocolate overpowered by the anise and licorice. The combo almost comes across like banana bread?  Tastes like it smells with the licorice upfront and a nice bitter toffee cocoa finish. I like this. I'm keeping one in the cellar. I think this will taste great with a little age and mellowing of the licorice. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Wow. What did I just taste!  Incredible aroma - bubble gum and cherry soda. Flavor is so smooth and delicious.  Clean crisp light with subtle fruit. There is no way this is over 10% - dangerously easy drinking. I can't wait to find this again - I'd drive all the way to the source in Buellton if I had to. Really amazing brew. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

beer_brewer_name: Port Brewing Co / The Lost Abbey
review_blob:
Pours pitch black with big brown head. Nice aroma of coffee, chocolate, toasty malt and alcohol. Nice flavor, smooth and hides the alcohol well, but this bottle has too much carbonation - foams up in the mouth. Takes away from the over all enjoyment of this beer.
 Think I will stir it up and let it sit a bit. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Poured from bomber into pint glass. Nice toasty dark IPA with big head. Sweet grape fruity piney aroma. Close your eyes and this could be just a regular yummy IPA. After a few sips you do notice the roasted malt backbone. Nice balance of hop and malt. I will be having this again soon. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Firestone Walker Wookey Jack Black Rye IPA

review_blob:
On tap at Library Ale House in Santa Monica. Nice golden pour into a tulip. Small fluffy head faded quickly. Amazing aroma for a lager. Smells more like a citrus hoppy IPA. Taste is a perfect blend of lager with spicy citrus hops. Crisp and bubbly with a great bitter finish.  Can't taste the 7%. I really like this unique tasting brew.  

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Poured from 22oz bottle into a pint glass. Rich dark amber color, cloudy with creamy dark head. Smells great with malty spicy notes. Taste is malty sweet caramel with nice finish. Smooth and tasty. I need to try this on tap next time. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Marin Old Dipsea Barleywine Style Ale

review_blob: Poured from Bomber to a  pint glass.  Great looking pour, creamy head.  Has the aroma you would expect from a DIPA - heavy on the pine.  Nice taste upfront, crisp hops, followed to quickly by a bitter finish.  The bitter lingers a bit to long on the aftertaste.  Not as smooth as some of my favorite DIPAs.  I really like the Big Daddy IPA so I was looking for more here.  Wishin I had grabbed a Maximus instead.
